### Clinical Effects
- Somatic motor dysfunction
- Autonomic dysregulation
- Cranial nerve dysfunction
- Skeletal muscle hyperactivity

## Clinical Presentation

### Grade I (Local)
- Pain at sting site
- Positive tap test
- Paresthesias

### Grade II (Local + Remote)
- Grade I plus remote pain/paresthesias

### Grade III (Systemic)
- Cranial nerve dysfunction
- Opsoclonus (roving eyes)
- Hypersalivation
- Slurred speech

### Grade IV (Severe)
- Skeletal muscle dysfunction
